io.raffi.JSON

Class JSONArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • java.util.ArrayList<JSONData>
          • io.raffi.JSON.JSONArray
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<JSONData>, java.util.Collection<JSONData>, java.util.List<JSONData>, java.util.RandomAccess

    public class JSONArray
extends java.util.ArrayList<JSONData>
    This class extends the ArrayList container class and it wraps it using the JSONData object. The add method is overloaded and it initialized a new JSONData object with the parameter data and adds it into the ArrayList. Calling the get method will simply return the JSONData object, while all the other get methods will cast the JSONData object as the appropriate type.
    Version:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Rafael Grigorian
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
